rcsim
-----
    Tool that can be used to send remote control commands without using
    the remote control :)

    It uses the input event-device, so works for all dbox2.
    
    Usage: rcsim <keyname> [<time>] [<repeat>]
    	<keyname> is one of the list below and corresponds to the key on the
	    dbox2-remote control
	<time> how long a code is repeatedly sent,
	    unit is seconds, default is 0 = sent only once
	<repeat> what time is waited until a new code is sent
	    (if <time> is greater than 0), unit is milliseconds,
	    default is 500

    Example: rcsim KEY_1 5 500
	sends KEY_1 for 5 seconds every 500 milliseconds
	    

    List of possible keynames:
	KEY_0,KEY_1,KEY_2,KEY_3,KEY_4,KEY_5,
	KEY_6,KEY_7,KEY_8,KEY_9,
	
	KEY_POWER,KEY_HOME,KEY_HELP,KEY_SETUP,
	KEY_OK,KEY_MUTE,
	KEY_RED,KEY_GREEN,KEY_YELLOW,KEY_BLUE,	

	KEY_VOLUMEUP,KEY_VOLUMEDOWN,

	KEY_RIGHT,KEY_LEFT,KEY_UP,KEY_DOWN,
	KEY_TOPLEFT,KEY_TOPRIGHT,KEY_BOTTOMLEFT,KEY_BOTTOMRIGHT,

	KEY_PAGEDOWN,KEY_PAGEUP,

